&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Penland Housekeepers support a welcoming and well-maintained campus by providing daily cleaning, room preparation, and basic upkeep of housing and workspaces for students, staff, instructors, and guests. Working closely with the services manager, this role helps ensure that campus facilities are clean, comfortable, safe, and ready for use year-round.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities include routine cleaning and sanitation, room turnovers, light maintenance tasks, inventory support, and responding to work orders. Housekeepers work both independently and as part of a team, use sound judgment to manage daily tasks, and contribute to a positive, respectful environment for the Penland community. This is a full-time, year-round position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;General:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the services manager to meet the housing needs of students, instructors, and guests and ensure a positive housing experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean and prepare rooms for students, instructors, and guests, maintaining high standards of cleanliness and organization in campus housing, including on room turnover days.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean offices, studio restrooms, meeting rooms, and other Penland workspaces as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform basic maintenance tasks in housing and promptly report mechanical or maintenance issues through the work order system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete assigned work orders in a timely manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow established safety rules and regulations, maintain a safe, clean work environment, and be familiar with all applicable material safety data sheets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a positive and respectful working relationship with students, staff, supervisors, and others encountered in the course of work.&lt;/li&gt;
